<section class="page-hero"><div class="page-width"><p class="eyebrow">The Science</p><h1 class="display">Less noise.<br>Better formulation.</h1><p>We kept Night Pack focused: three ingredients, clear doses, and no melatonin.</p></div></section><section class="editorial"><div class="page-width editorial-grid"><aside><p class="section-kicker">The thinking</p><h2>Support the transition from overstimulated to settled.</h2></aside><article><h3>Why keep it simple?</h3><p>Better formulas are not necessarily formulas with more ingredients. Night Pack focuses on a small number of well-known ingredients with roles in relaxation and stress support, at clear daily doses.</p><h3>Magnesium Bisglycinate &amp; Citrate Chelate</h3><p>Magnesium is involved in normal muscle and nervous system function. We use two forms selected for daily use and practical capsule volume.</p><h3>L-Theanine</h3><p>L-Theanine is an amino acid naturally found in tea. It is commonly used in evening routines to support a calm, relaxed mental state.</p><h3>Ashwagandha Extract</h3><p>Ashwagandha is a root extract traditionally used to support stress resilience. Night Pack uses <em>Withania somnifera</em> root extract at 250mg.</p><h3>Why no melatonin?</h3><p>We deliberately chose a melatonin-free formula. Night Pack is about building a calmer wind-down routine, rather than positioning the product as a sedative.</p><p style="font-size:13px;color:#746879">This page is educational and not medical advice. Validate all copy and claims against final regulatory review before publication.</p></article></div></section>{% schema %}{"name":"Science page","settings":[]}{% endschema %}